content:
Change agents' queues and skills as needed on the Agent tab in Omni Supervisor. 

Available in Lightning Experience, Essentials, Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions.

To create or change queues: 
Manage Queue Memberships, Customize Application, and Manage Public List Views.
To change queues created by other users: 
Manage Queue Memberships, Customize Application, and Manage Public List Views and Manage Users.
To change skills: 
Create, read, update on service resources, Read access and Edit access for the Active field on Service Resource field-level security, Read access and Edit access for the End Date, Start Date, and Skill Level fields on Service Resource Skill field-level security.

Open the Agents tab in Omni Supervisor. To change the queues to which agents are assigned, select the agents, and then click Change Queues.
To change the skills assigned to agents, select the agents, and then click Change Skills.
title: Configuring Agent Queues and Skills in Service Cloud
